]. A general chart of these values as a function of cooling

, the model predictions are found to be very accurate to a wide range of AlZnMg(Cu)
alloys and the total speciﬁc precipitation enthalpy generally decreases with increasing cooling rate for
all alloys. A high level of similarity to the AlMgSi alloys is found for the general kinetic behaviour.
However, the speciﬁc enthalpy values, as well as the obtainable hardness values, are generally higher
for the 7xxx alloys. This is reasonable, as the latter contain higher concentrations of alloying elements.
